The paper deals with image processing and machine learning techniques to selectively use high resolution data while reducing acquisition and run-time cost. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of reinforcement learning also suggests that the paper could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The focus on identifying when and where to use high resolution data suggests that the paper could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning techniques suggests that the paper could belong to the deep learning (cs.DL) sub-category.
